\id GEN 01-GEN-asv.sfm The American Standard Version of the Holy Bible (1901) Tuesday, September 12, 2006
\ide UTF-8
\h Genesis 
\toc1 The First Book of Moses, called Genesis 
\toc2 Genesis 
\toc3 Gen 
\mt1 The First Book of Moses, called Genesis 
\c 1  
\p
\v 1 In the beginning God created the heavens and the earth. 
\v 2 And the earth was waste and void; and darkness was upon the face of the deep: and the Spirit of God moved upon the face of
the waters. 
\v 3 And God said, Let there be light: and there was light. 
\v 4 And God saw the light, that it was good: and God divided the light from the darkness.
\v 5 And God called the light Day, and the darkness he called Night. And there was evening and there was morning, one day.
